The OpenFISMA project is an open source application designed to reduce the 
complexity and automate the regulatory requirements of the Federal Information 
Security Management Act (FISMA) and the National Institute of Standards and 
Technology (NIST) Risk Management Framework (RMF). 

Please see the following resources for more information:

Installation:
http://manual.openfisma.org/display/OPENFISMA/Installation+Guide

Website:
http://openfisma.org

License: 
http://openfisma.org/content/license

Documentation: 
http://manual.openfisma.org
http://documentation.openfisma.org
http://api.openfisma.org

Issue Tracking/Build Status:
http://jira.openfisma.org (Bug reports, feature requests)
http://crucible.openfisma.org (Peer code review, source code browser)
http://bamboo.openfisma.org (Continuous Integration)

Help:
Please visit the forums at http://openfisma.org/forum or email openfisma@endeavorsystems.com
